Steps to add Tailwind to a file.

1.Create an empty folder in vs code.
2.open terminal then enter npm init
3.after that step enter npm i vite.
4.Then in terminal enter: npm install -D tailwindcss postcss autoprefixer
5.After that enter: npx tailwindcss init
6. create postcss.config.js file and add this code:module.exports = {
    plugins: {
      tailwindcss: {},
      autoprefixer: {},
    }
  }
7.In tailwind config.js file write: 
module.exports = {
  content: ["*"],
  theme: {
    extend: {},
  },
  plugins: [],
}

8.Create main.css file and write : @tailwind base;
@tailwind components;
@tailwind utilities;
8. create html file and link css file .
9. in terminal enter: npm start
